  <description type="morphology">Shrubs or trees, 20–40(–70) dm, &lt;usually branched to base&gt;. Leaves: blade broadly ovate to deltate, 3–7 cm, length/width = 1–1.2, lobes 2–4 per side, distinct, lobe apex acute, base very broadly cuneate or truncate to weakly subcordate, adaxial surface glabrous, sometimes sparsely appressed-hairy along veins. Inflorescence branches glabrous. Flowers 15–22 mm diam.; stamens 20, anthers pale pink.</description>
